## Resources & Hotlines

### If You're Concerned About Someone

**United States:**
- **FBI Tip Line**: 1-800-CALL-FBI / tips.fbi.gov
- **National Counterterrorism Center**: www.nctc.gov
- **Parents for Peace** (family support): www.parentsforpeace.com

**United Kingdom:**
- **Prevent Program**: www.preventtragedies.co.uk / 0800 011 3764
- **Families Against Terrorism**: www.familiesagainstterrorism.org

**Canada:**
- **Canada Centre for Community Engagement**: www.publicsafety.gc.ca
- **RCMP National Security**: 1-800-420-5805

**European Union:**
- **RAN (Radicalisation Awareness Network)**: ec.europa.eu/ran
- **Hotlines by country**: ec.europa.eu/home-affairs/what-we-do/networks/radicalisation_awareness_network_en

### If You Want to Leave Extremism

**Exit Programs:**
- **Life After Hate** (U.S., former extremists): www.lifeafterhate.org
- **ExitUSA** (neo-Nazis): www.exitusa.org
- **Quilliam Foundation** (UK, Islamist extremism): www.quilliamfoundation.org
- **Hayat** (Germany, families + former extremists): www.hayat-deutschland.de

**Anonymous counseling:**
- Many programs offer **confidential** support (not reported to authorities unless imminent violence)

